text: Białogard () is a town in West Pomeranian Voivodeship in northwestern Poland. It is the capital of Białogard County. About 23,000 people live there. Its area is 25.73 km². It is the birthplace of Aleksander Kwaśniewski, 3rd President of Poland (1995–2005). Category:Towns in West Pomeranian Voivodeship
title: Białogard
